	pages = {917-948},
	abstract = {External sources of as-if randomness -- that is, external instruments -- can be used to identify the dynamic causal effects of macroeconomic shocks. One method is a oneâ€ step instrumental variables regression (local projections -- IV); a more efficient twoâ€ step method involves a vector autoregression. We show that, under a restrictive instrument validity condition, the oneâ€ step method is valid even if the vector autoregression is not invertible, so comparing the two estimates provides a test of invertibility. If, however, lagged endogenous variables are needed as control variables in the one-step method, then the conditions for validity of the two methods are the same. },
